               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1276" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1276" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1276" type="surname" value="BRIND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1276" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BRIND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a patten-maker, and work for Mr. Dibb. in Union-street, four doors from the prosecutor's. On the 16th of July, about ten o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner in the act of coming out of the prosecutor's window with a coat in his hand—I never saw him before—I took hold of him, and took the coat from him—he said that I had put him in at the window, which is false.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I did not say he had put me in at the window—he says he found the coat in my hand, and he took it off the bed himself when he took me. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I did not; I took it from him—there was another one with him at the time, but he went away as soon as the alarm was given by my brother, who saw him get in at the window.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1277" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1277" type="surname" value="BRIND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1277" type="given" value="JOSIAH"></interp>JOSIAH BRIND</persName>
                  </hi>. I work at the same shop as my brother. I was on the leads, and saw the prisoner open the prosecutor's parlour window, and get in—I called my brother—he did not hear at first—I called him again; and he went and took the prisoner just as he was coming out at the window with the coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1278" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1278" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1278" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1278" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE CLARK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a tailor, and live in this house—this is my cat (<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>)—it was left hanging on the parlour door—I know nothing of the prisoner—he had no right in my house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-1279" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1279" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1279" type="surname" value="HODGES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-1279" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS HODGES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I took the prisoner into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> As I was coming along, a man took off my cap, and threw it in the window—I knocked at the door—nobody answered, the window being open, I went in to get it, and as I was coming on again, the man collared me.</p>
